Ansible - Written in Python, agent-less, utilizes an imperative (rather than declarative) approach.
    
    Chef - Written in Ruby, also relies on an imperative config management approach.
    Puppet - Relies on a declarative config management approach, using a domain-specific language and an agent/master architecture.
